I did not know this, but Hanukkah is actually a celebration of the Maccabean Revolt, but if you're an apostolic Christian 1 Maccabees and 2 Maccabees are canonical texts of the Bible. And then if you're an Orthodox Christian you technically get 3 Maccabees and 4 Maccabees too.

Good opportunity to take to familiarize ourselves with an overlooked part of our Scripture. You have lots of themes like the Maccabeans discussing the Sabbath and breaking it by fighting on that day to survive that later appear in the New Testament too.

Undertale perfectly captures how it feels to be at a small mountain resort town in winter. Endless pine trees covered in snow in the distance, large dogs off their leash who are probably pretty friendly but still somewhat terrifying when they bark at you, hickchud locals around.
When I'm walking through a pine forest or coming around the outskirts of a village and see the cozy houses with the locals busying themselves in their yards I always think of Snowdin.
